events.name: LA Clippers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 28 points and the Los Angeles Clippers rang up the highest point total of the season against the NBA's leading defense, beating the New York Knicks 129-115 on Sunday for their 10th win in 11 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard, Clippers pull away from Knicks for 129-115 win

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic matched his career high with 47 points and the fast-starting Denver Nuggets beat Utah 128-117 on Sunday to end the Jazz’s winning streak at 11.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 47 points, Nuggets end Jazz winning streak at 11

headlines.description: — Tobias Harris scored 27 points and Furkan Korkmaz added 17, including the go-ahead baskets in the fourth quarter, to help the Philadelphia 76ers complete a frantic rally Sunday night with a 119-110 victory over the Indiana Pacers.
headlines.shortLinkText: 76ers find finishing touch to rally past Pacers, 119-110

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 30 points and 10 rebounds to lead the Toronto Raptors to a 115-102 win over the Orlando Magic on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors snap 3-game losing streak, beat Raptors 115-102

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal and Russell Westbrook hit 3-pointers in a wild 3.8-second sequence in the final seconds to help the Washington Wizards stun Kevin Durant and the Brooklyn Nets 149-146 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook, Beal hit late 3s, Wizards stunt Nets 149-146

headlines.description: — Malik Beasley scored 23 points and rookie Anthony Edwards finished with 23 in his second straight start as the Minnesota Timberwolves held on to beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 109-104 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: T-Wolves snap 3-game slide with 109-104 win over Cavaliers
